LangID.Text: Apple CarPlay allows the secure use of an iPhone device in this car. The connection can be established via USB or wireless. The settings for a later wireless connection are configured automatically during the first connection via USB. Alternatively, a wireless connection can be manually set. Please make sure that your Bluetooth access point is activated and connect the iPhone to the car. Please mind any necessary confirmations on your iPhone.

CarLife allows the secure use of a phone in this car. The connection can be established via USB or wireless. Please install the CarLife App from the App-Store on your phone. Please mind any necessary confirmations on your phone.
MirrorLink allows the secure use of a phone provided with MirrorLink technology in this car. The connection can be established via USB. Please mind any necessary confirmations on your phone.

An overview of other apps can be found
at https://www.skoda.com.cn/apps/index.html
or by scanning the code with your mobile
device.

This function maintains the distance to the vehicle ahead while\ntaking the set speed into account.
These notes support a proactive driving style.
This function detects possible signs of driver fatigue based on\nsteering behavior, time of day and driving time, and gives a visual\nand acoustic warning.
This function assesses critical traffic situations and prepares for\na possible accident by tightening the front seat belts and closing\nthe windows up to a gap.
This function gives a visual and acoustic notification as soon as the\nvehicle ahead starts driving again.
This function helps you to minimize potential rear-end collisions and\naccidents with vehicles and pedestrians, or to avoid them in the\nbest case scenario.
This function detects when the vehicle is no longer being actively\ncontrolled and takes over partial control (of the vehicle) until it is\nstationary in the current lane.
This function uses corrective steering to alert the driver if the\nvehicle unintentionally leaves the lane.
By using visual signals in the exterior mirrors, this function\nindicates vehicles that could be a potential hazard when\nchanging lanes.
This function uses rear radar sensors to monitor the area behind\nand next to the vehicle. This allows for vehicles within a 20 meter\nrange to be detected.
This function makes it possible to factor in a trailer while route\nplanning and to also display the relevant road signs depending on\nthe set maximum speed.

correct, press "SET".

The pressure in all 4 tires must be checked and set correctly in order for
the Tire Pressure Monitoring System to function correctly. Depending on
the vehicle, the tire pressures are found on the sticker located on either
the inside of the fuel door or in the driver door frame. For additional
information on tire pressures and the Tire Pressure Monitoring System,
refer to your Owner's Manual. Once you have checked the pressure in all
4 tires and have made any necessary adjustments, press "SET" in the
"Tire Pressure Monitoring System" screen. The vehicle will start the
programming process.

This function maintains the distance to the vehicle ahead while taking the set speed into account.

This function helps you to minimize potential rear-end collisions and accidents with vehicles and pedestrians, or to avoid them in the best case scenario.
This function detects when the vehicle is no longer being actively controlled and takes over partial control (of the vehicle) until it is stationary in the current lane.
This function uses corrective steering to alert the driver if the vehicle unintentionally leaves the lane.
By using visual signals in the exterior mirrors, this function indicates vehicles that could be a potential hazard when changing lanes.
This function uses rear radar sensors to monitor the area behind and next to the vehicle. This allows for vehicles within a 20 meter range to be detected.
This function makes it possible to factor in a trailer while route planning and to also display the relevant road signs depending on the set maximum speed.
These notes support a proactive driving style.
This function detects possible signs of driver fatigue based on steering behavior, time of day and driving time, and gives a visual and acoustic warning.
This function assesses critical traffic situations and prepares for a possible accident by tightening the front seat belts and closing the windows up to a gap.
